I am trying to synthesize a verilog code generated by Bluespec Systemverilog Compiler. 

### Part of generated Verilog code causing error
```verilog
module ConvertFromZ( IN, OUT);
   parameter width = 1;
   input [width - 1 : 0]       IN;
   output [width - 1 : 0]      OUT;
   tri [width - 1 : 0]  BUS;   //error in this line
   assign BUS = IN;
   assign OUT = BUS;
endmodule
```
### Error Message
```src/ConvertFromZ.v:14: ERROR: syntax error, unexpected '[', expecting TOK_ID or '#'```

Any help would be appreciated. Thanks!

